   204	def detect_subject_object_overlap(subject_str: str, object_str: str, string_similarity_threshold: float) -> bool:
   205	    """Determine whether there is overlap between a subject and an object in a statement.
   206	
   207	    If either of them is contained in the other when cast to lowercase, return True.
   208	
   209	    Otherwise, return True iff the **cased** normalized jaro-winkler similarity between the two
   210	    if lower than the specified threshold.
   211	    """
   212	    assert isinstance(subject_str, str)
   213	    assert isinstance(object_str, str)
   214	
   215	    if (subject_str.lower() in object_str.lower()) or (object_str.lower() in subject_str.lower()):
   216	        return True
   217	
   218	    return JaroWinkler.normalized_similarity(subject_str, object_str) >= string_similarity_threshold
